toValue(Object) - Static method in class com.google.mu.protobuf.util.MoreStructs
Converts object to Value according to the following rules: Primitive types (numbers, strings, booleans) and Struct proto types (Struct, ListValue etc.) are wrapped inside the respective Value wrapper protos; null and NullValue are converted to NullValue; Value is returned as is; Optional of primitive types, Value or struct proto types is unwrapped then converted, with the empty() instance converted to NullValue; Collection (Iterable, Map, Multimap, Table)s are recursively converted.
